00:09:29.506 --> 00:09:32.036 A:middle
Or you can zoom in
to get more details.

00:09:35.336 --> 00:09:37.896 A:middle
The information density
and the lines

00:09:37.896 --> 00:09:40.046 A:middle
that we show changes
at each zoom.

00:09:40.796 --> 00:09:43.756 A:middle
Now, some people may want
to have different choices.

00:09:44.166 --> 00:09:46.156 A:middle
So, for example,
they may want to see

00:09:46.156 --> 00:09:47.556 A:middle
if a bus route is available.

00:09:48.096 --> 00:09:52.636 A:middle
In our product, you can select
the exact vehicles that you'd

00:09:52.636 --> 00:09:53.806 A:middle
like to use for your journey.

00:09:54.846 --> 00:09:56.856 A:middle
Here is a competing bus route.

00:09:57.916 --> 00:09:59.986 A:middle
Now, we didn't recommend
this because it takes longer.

00:10:00.486 --> 00:10:03.986 A:middle
But it's an option
that's available to you.

00:10:04.696 --> 00:10:08.536 A:middle
So let's go back to our
BART route and examine

00:10:08.536 --> 00:10:09.716 A:middle
that in greater detail.

00:10:13.776 --> 00:10:16.726 A:middle
The route planner tells you when
to leave, how long it will take,

00:10:16.726 --> 00:10:17.946 A:middle
and gives a summary
of the route.

00:10:18.386 --> 00:10:20.636 A:middle
Tapping on this, I get
what we call the list view.

00:10:21.256 --> 00:10:23.266 A:middle
A detailed list of
instructions to follow.

00:10:23.956 --> 00:10:26.736 A:middle
I can expand the list
of stops if I'd like.

00:10:29.796 --> 00:10:33.106 A:middle
Now, when I select start,
I enter guided navigation

00:10:33.106 --> 00:10:34.416 A:middle
with detailed instructions.

00:10:34.746 --> 00:10:36.056 A:middle
Since I'm already
at the airport,

00:10:36.096 --> 00:10:37.656 A:middle
